rComments: Overall an amazing professor!

Mary is a really nice person. She is very interested in plants, ecology and environmental issues; so for this specific course, she's very passionate and a good lecturer. She gives extra information on her lectures that are not on the slides, so going to class is important to succeed in this course.

Extremely helpful and doesn't try to trick her students. She's passionate in what she teaches and always tries to make the content understandable for her students. Probably one of the more engaging professors in human sciences

Amazing prof!! she is very happy go lucky kinda of person, always smiling when she lectures. She gave AMAZING advice on how to study for university bio exams, even useful for upper years, so do listen carefully!! Overall, straight-forward exams and great prof :)
She kinda babbles too much i think. except for that she is a good teacher.
awesome

She's a really sweet person, and though she doesn't finish her lectures sometimes, her lecture slides are really good. focus on her lecture slides and take notes on her slides on what she says in lecture! Textbook is okay, but only use it if you don't get anything in lecture itself. :) she's really helpful in office hours!
Very nice, straightforward, knows material inside out

Took plants with her. It is her field of expertise so she was very excited about it... However, she stammered a lot and was always rifling through her notes and the course textbook like she didn't know what she was talking about! I suggest reading the textbook thoroughly if you intend on doing well but focus on what she covers in class!
She's sweet and helpful during office hours. Not the most engaging of lecturers though. Her exams are fair; difficult, but fair. Just be meticulous in studying and you should be fine.

She's a very sweet prof and if you go to her during office hours she explains things well,  but her powerpoints are very hard to study and half the stuff that she had on her powerpoints didnt even come on the exam!!!! So u have to make sure you study your book. Module 2 in my opinion was the best part of the course!

Easy class. If you actually study, manage your time, listen to her lectures and note down all the hints she gives you, you will do great! I can understand that for some she might be boring, but if you have a passion for biology you will love the class. Her exams are so easy compared to a lot of other profs!
Boring. Not enthusiastic. Her notes suck. No point in downloading them or coming to class. Promised things she could not keep.

Exams are challenging. If you are looking to boost up your GPA ..forget it! Questions on exam are based on 'connecting the dots' and blind memorization to score A is out of the question. A LOT!!! of material has been packed into the 3 months and not sure why so much depth is require at intro levels. Goodluck!
Great Prof! Really helpful during office hours and is really approachable. Overall great!

Ok prof. not very enthusiastic about the material. I picked up a few mistakes she said during the class, nothing crucial though. Her fatalistic view of things made em laugh. Her midterm and exams were EASY! Read the textbook, forget her lecture- get an A.

Took both BIOA01 and BIOA02. She came for the ending of A01 and beginning of A02. Very nice prof, and helpful if you go to office hours. Focus on understanding material for exam. Reading through lecture slides a few days before dsnt help.I found watching lectures over again and refering to slides/book was useful for exam. Gives study guide 4 exam
a really great professor, clear and concise and extremely helpful!

She is probably the best professor I've had at UTSC! Her lecture material is very clear and reflects the textbook to a T; if you really pay attention in her classes and make the effort to approach her during office hours with questions, you'll get PLENTY of tips for exam questions, lab reports, etc. FAVOURITE PROF !!! :)

Great professor--highly recommended that you go to her office hours because she really shines with respect to the advice that she gives (she gave me hints as well as to what to expect for the exam). Exams were tough but fair, but she tends to ramble during her lectures, pushing her to rush at the end of each hour. Overall, a good professor.
Shes a sweetheart =) you dont even have to go to the lectures, just read the txtb and memorize her lec notes and its an easy 80+

I love Olaveson she's so sweet and cares about the students! Her slides were really helpful, I mainly relied on them for the exam. Exam was very fair. She wasn't really that entertaining so I lost focus often, but I think that's more my fault than it is hers. I felt that she could have spread the material better throughout the semester though
I've had her for 3 courses now and I find that her exams are really fair and straightforward! She's quite helpful as well.

The lecture material is RIDICULOUSLY BORING so I guess there's not much Olaveson could have done with it. She's a kind professor but seriously needs to work on her organization skills. Exams are fair but challenging.

she really made the plant physio midterm hard! Not to mention she crammed a lot of information in.....like if you can't cover something for the midterm..save it for the final..her so called "supplemental slides" were as long as her lectures! O and she didn't give us enough time for the midterm...what is up with the vague exam questions??

I took this course along with BGYA02 in the summer. I found it very easy because of the professor. She knows what she's talking about when she lectures and her exams are fair-I wish I had her in other bio courses as well

I liked her for A01/A02 but she seriously could not manage BGYB10. There was too much material for her to cover and she ended up rushing everything towards the end. Her lectures were boring too! On the bright side, her exams were fair.
She was a nice proff and I really enjoyed her lectures. (H)

she had difficulty controlling the class but shes very helpful and provides hints throughout semester be sure to sit in the front so you can hear them since ppl talk alot in lecture. if she doesnt discuss it in class it wont be on exam, exams are straightforward fairly easy. clicker questions and mc questions at end of each chpt may show up on exam
theeeeeee best :D

great prof for A01, probably the worst prof I ever had for plant physio (B31). Extremely dry lectures, and she really did not know the material herself. Exams are difficult and the textbook does not make it easier.

i think she is reallyyyy sweet!!! n soo helpful!! her lectures are not the best...i mean they get really boring at times...but the students already know most of the stuff from grade 12..sooo over all...its not soo bad!! plus she tries her best...soooo i liked her :))

Please rely LESS on your slides, move around more to keep your students' attention, and don't go too slow on the introductory slides, then rush the ones towards the end that require a lot of explanation, and finally leave the left over slides (often involving tedious processes) for us to memorize. Exams are fair.

She seems like a very nice person but I always tend to zone out in lectures. Study her notes but make sure you read the textbook. Also, I made the mistake of not going to lectures because some of the material on the exam was unheard of. If you do that, you will be fine.
Notes are on the short side and way too insufficient for exams. Attend lectures and take notes; she gives hints. Read the text and take notes; hers aren't enough.
she seems like a very sweet person. I like the study guides. As a lab coordinator, she's great. it seems like she really cares about the students which is nice:). I wish bio only had 1 prof not two:(
She is very good at teaching biology, the slides are awesome. Gives hints in lectures, so it's beneficial to show up.
She's extremely helpful and her notes are very organized ... her exams are also fair! I don't like biology but her method of tecahing made me like biology. Million thanks to her!

Awesome teacher, her slides are extremely organized and clear, she makes even the most complicated of processes very simplistic... Very willing to help, she doesn't mind if you go to her in her office and ask her the most random or long questions. Great with answering emails. Her background of genetics, etc was not as good as plants, her passion :)

Dude. She's so awesome. Teaches at a slower pace than what I'm used to, but that's okay. Her jokes are witty, and her research is pretty cool. She CAN generate an interest for plants.  She's very clear, and is there to help. Exams are pretty straightforward. You'll have a good time in this class.
she is ok i think... hope i pass the course though
Amazing Professor. If you know your grade 12 bio you'll love her class. Very witty also great smart jokes.
good prof, but i think her pace is too slow
nice teacher, taught me nuff stuff
Dont bother thinking twice. Shes an AWESOME prof. She is clear. She's interesting. Helpful! Her exams are straightforward. I cant think of any cons. You are going to love her and this course.
She makes really good lecture notes that highlights what is important in the textbook. I also find her a very approchable prof.
She reads from the slides, doesn't explain them, and takes the material on her slides directly from the text book. Why, oh WHY did I pay $418 to hear her read a text book to me?!
She makes the best lecture notes ever, there's basically no need to read the textbook if you understand the lecture and the notes provided. The lab work and the exams were fair and easy.
I think she is fairly funny, as well as being a good instructor.
The course work is demanding, but Professor Olaveson is great. Very hardworking and passionate about her subject.

Very good prof!  Her notes are AMAZING.  I practically didn't even have to go to class since her notes were so organized.  She provides a study guide for the midterm and the final which makes the course so much easier and less time consuming.

she is a very nice professor. she teaches all the materials in detail. her exams are fair. she is always in a smiling mood. even when students talk during lectures, she tells them to be quiet in a very nice manner. one of the best professors in u of T.
Great prof, I was in the wrong program and she went out of her way to get me into BIO. She has no eyebrows though.
Really nice teacher.. clear and on task :D
good teacher, makes everything easy to understand
indeed a great prof for bio..one of the best at UTSC...
SHe's very nice...but the final exam was tough, but fair. I found it tough because I didn't study enough.
Final was a KILLER !!!!
i dont know if its becoz i didnt study enough, i think the final exam was a killer! but the prof is really nice.
You cannot get a better prof than her! :)

This teacher needs to incorporate more of her own knowledge and examples in her lectures other than just reading the powerpoint slides every lecture.  Other than that, she is quite descent and replies emails in a timely manner.
Well, I really enjoy her lecture, but her test is kind of difficult because you can't just memorize the concept, you have to apply the concept to various case study and do from there.
professor olvaeson is a very generous and kind lady. She explains every questions clearly. i like her very much. she is a good pro.
She's really nice, and she'll go at a pace where anyone is able to keep up, doesn't matter even if we know the stuff! Very helpful! best prof so Far!!

best prof of my first semester at UTSC. she is very helpful. her slides are super! and i appreciate her study guide, it is very clear in it what she is expecting us to know for the term test. EXCELLENT prof!
fair exam, very nice, lectures boring, but she prepared good lecture slides
I admit that she was a bit boring (sp. compared to hasenkamph), but very very helpful! her exam was damn easy too....
Taught evolution part of the term reasonably. Lectures were quite boring, but bearable. The zoo trip was very amusing. Exam went well too, straight forward and a bit easy.

She is not a bad professor at all! She clearly defines what you need to know for exams and for that I am very happy. Because of this, u can be fully prepared for the exams and be ready to do very well
All of you people have no appreciation of how hlepful SHE REALLY WAS!!! She would help you out with anything, very nice and sweet lady!!! SHE WAS THE BEST!!!

BORING! her lectures are useless; she will put you to sleep.  hasemkampf is the greatest teacher of all time; she teaches and shows plenty more effort.  olaveson reads directly from her pp slides becase she thinks we can't read.  no study guide.  BORING!
Very Nice Prof. much better than hasenkampf

I don't think she is better than Hasenkampf, she seems to be just repeating the slides without any stress , which make me sleepy, Hasenkampf seems to be more teaching you telling you what the stuffs are , that saves me time
she is okay..but she makes some of the concepts hard even though they are not..but overall much better than hasenkampf!
she is okay..but she makes some of the concepts hard even though they are not..but overall much better than hasenkampf!
Power slides are extremly helpful, you can just listen to what she has to say and not try to write madly, but slides aren't on the intranet on time.

i think she is a good prof. i just don't like the fact that some ppl choose to speak through her lecture. they are probably grade 12s who need a year to mature. i am paying money to hear her lecture so shut up and GET OUT!!!
Very clear and precise with good overall presentation of slides. Not very enthusiastic though, but doesn't really matter.
She seems really nice, and doesn't go too fast. Everything is explained clearly, and the powerpoint notes online are very useful.
